  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_456586316" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/456586316" />
    <a title="Brianna Lee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9708137-brianna-lee"><img alt="Brianna Lee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1603217871p2/9708137.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/456586316?book_show_action=true">Nov 15, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brianna Lee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brianna Lee" href="/user/show/9708137-brianna-lee">Brianna Lee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9708137-brianna-lee?shelf=high-school-age">high-school-age</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9708137-brianna-lee?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9708137-brianna-lee?shelf=r2r">r2r</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer456586316" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18009001118503149969">I received this book from the author in exchange for an honest review.<br/><br/>This book is great! Danielle Sibarium is truly a talented writer! “Heart Waves” had me from the beginning and kept me sucked in the entire time. I absolutely loved that the author combined my favorite genres into one story: Contemporary Romance and Paranormal. It was Young Adult, which I love too! I give this book 5 STARS because it was just awesome in every way!<br/><br/>Jenna, the main character of “Heart Waves,” is the same as most o</span>
  <span id="freeText18009001118503149969" style="display:none">I received this book from the author in exchange for an honest review.<br /><br />This book is great! Danielle Sibarium is truly a talented writer! “Heart Waves” had me from the beginning and kept me sucked in the entire time. I absolutely loved that the author combined my favorite genres into one story: Contemporary Romance and Paranormal. It was Young Adult, which I love too! I give this book 5 STARS because it was just awesome in every way!<br /><br />Jenna, the main character of “Heart Waves,” is the same as most other teenage girls her age…except that she has a gift. Jenna knows things other people don’t, and she can pick up personal information just by touching something, such as a piece of jewelry. While at a party, Jenna meets a boy named Reece and she instantly falls for him. They have an immediate connection and want to see where their chemistry will lead. However, there is one small problem…from the moment they met, Jenna learned of a prediction that Reece was going to break her heart. Jenna spends a lot of her relationship with Reece waiting for the other shoe to drop – waiting to see if Reece was really going to break her heart. <br /><br />I loved the characters of Danielle Sibarium’s “Heart Waves” so much! Jenna and Reece were absolutely amazing, and I enjoyed everything about them. I was routing for their love and wanted to see them happy, but I was nervous throughout the entire story waiting to see if the prediction was going to come true. I think that “Heart Waves” is a story for many people. I would recommend it to young adult and adult readers, as well as Contemporary Romance and Paranormal fans. As a Paranormal fan, I enjoyed the Paranormal twist. But, for people that do not normally read Paranormal books…don’t worry! Of course, it is a part of the story but it isn’t the main focus. The Romance is more the main point. Therefore, Danielle Sibarium’s “Heart Waves” is a novel that will please readers from several different genres. This 5 STAR book by this talented author is a story that you will want to read! I also really enjoyed another novel by Ms. Sibarium, called “For Always” which was great. Go out and add Ms. Danielle Sibarium’s work to your ‘To Be Read’ list now if “Heart Waves” and “For Always” are not already on it. If they are on your list…then what are you waiting for?! I also look forward to reading the next installment in this series, “Breaking Waves.”<br /><br />Brianna Lee Book Reviews<br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.briannaleereviews.blogspot.com">http://www.briannaleereviews.blogspot...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="18009001118503149969" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


