<div id="review_348089481" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/348089481" />
    <a title="Megan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5208301-megan"><img alt="Megan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1386943356p2/5208301.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/348089481?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Megan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Megan" href="/user/show/5208301-megan">Megan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer348089481" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10593891026174361260">This book was so great! I generally go for paranormal books, but I mixed things up a bit recently by trying out some YA contemporary books. So far I have read two and I have not been disappointed!<br/><br/>Heart Waves could technically be considered paranormal, because it does have a touch of it... But because its not a main focus in the book, I am not going to consider it from tha genre.<br/><br/>There are so many amazing characters in this book! Danielle Sibarium has done a fantastic job in creating all of them a</span>
  <span id="freeText10593891026174361260" style="display:none">This book was so great! I generally go for paranormal books, but I mixed things up a bit recently by trying out some YA contemporary books. So far I have read two and I have not been disappointed!<br /><br />Heart Waves could technically be considered paranormal, because it does have a touch of it... But because its not a main focus in the book, I am not going to consider it from tha genre.<br /><br />There are so many amazing characters in this book! Danielle Sibarium has done a fantastic job in creating all of them and really bringing them to life.<br /><br />Jenna and Grace are your typical teenage girls, other then the fact that Jenna can pick things up from people's belongings... Kind of being psychic I guess.<br /><br />Grace was slightly annoying because I have never really liked girls like her. Mike was awesome! (don't forget to check out my interview with Mike that I had so much fun doing!) Mike is a jock, a jerk, and so incredibly adorable! I loved him!<br /><br />Then there is Reece, for some reason he bugged me... He always seemed to try too hard to be perfect for Jenna, and he has a major temper which is totally uncool. He also seems like he is hiding something and although it's never told to us what he is hiding, at the end of the book it is super obvious that is something pretty major.<br /><br />The one thing I did Like about Reece though, is that he brought Tyler into the story... Not too much, only a few little bits but OMG I love him! He is a bad boy with a sob story history, and well duh he is super hot as well!<br /><br />Overall it was a fantastic first book in the series, and I can not wait until the second comes out because I want to learn more about Tyler... Well and everyone else as well... Oh and I also really want to know what is going to happen between Jenna and Tyler they seemed to have some MAJOR chemistry right off the bat so that should definitely be interesting in the next book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10593891026174361260" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


