<div id="review_1193855577" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1193855577" />
    <a title="Brigitte " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34807917-brigitte"><img alt="Brigitte " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1604558413p2/34807917.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1193855577?book_show_action=true">Feb 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brigitte " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brigitte " href="/user/show/34807917-brigitte">Brigitte </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20326610-heart-waves">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34807917-brigitte?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/34807917-brigitte?shelf=paranormal">paranormal</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1193855577" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10413857240373513148">Jenna is a seventeen year old student who doesn&apos;t trust guys much due to some rumours and misunderstanding, which put her off dating. She is also called the &quot;Ice Queen&quot; because of her attitude towards the boys. <br/><br/>Reece is a nineteen year old who meets Jenna at her neighbour&apos;s party. Jenna has a gift, whereby she can hold objects belonging to other individuals and pick up on their energy. After giving what she thinks is the last of her readings, Reece approaches her and hands her his ring and asks </span>
  <span id="freeText10413857240373513148" style="display:none">Jenna is a seventeen year old student who doesn't trust guys much due to some rumours and misunderstanding, which put her off dating. She is also called the "Ice Queen" because of her attitude towards the boys. <br /><br />Reece is a nineteen year old who meets Jenna at her neighbour's party. Jenna has a gift, whereby she can hold objects belonging to other individuals and pick up on their energy. After giving what she thinks is the last of her readings, Reece approaches her and hands her his ring and asks for a reading. They take one look at each other and instantly there is an undeniable attraction between them, but what Jenna predicts is enough to make her want to run a mile. <br /><br />Reece will not be deterred and pursues her relentlessly until she gives in and agrees to date him. Everything feels so right between them but every now and again, something will crop up to give Jenna cause for concerns. Even though they agree to be honest with each other and trust each other, Reece appears to have secrets he is not prepared to share with Jenna. Whatever it is, indicates that it involves his ex girlfriend Becca and his ex best friend Tyler, but nothing conclusive. <br /><br />There is love and laughter as well as tears and doubts throughout this part of the story. It ends on a note which left me wanting for more and I am glad that I don't have to wait for long as the next part is already available. This is an easy to read, Young Adult Romance with a touch of the Paranormal and would appeal to those who hold an interest in this genre.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10413857240373513148" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


