        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1038846040" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3268216962101132725">I was sent this book for an honest review and let me tell you it was AMAZING! Yes Amazing. I couldn&apos;t put it down. I actually read the whole series in 2 days. Yes all 3 books in 2 days. That should tell you how amazing this book and series is.<br/>But I&apos;m here for this book.<br/>Gah I loved the characters first and formost. Reece was so prefect he fought for Jenna. He refused to let them not be together, even when things get rough and rocky he is there every step. Jenna was so strong willed and full of li</span>
  <span id="freeText3268216962101132725" style="display:none">I was sent this book for an honest review and let me tell you it was AMAZING! Yes Amazing. I couldn't put it down. I actually read the whole series in 2 days. Yes all 3 books in 2 days. That should tell you how amazing this book and series is.<br />But I'm here for this book.<br />Gah I loved the characters first and formost. Reece was so prefect he fought for Jenna. He refused to let them not be together, even when things get rough and rocky he is there every step. Jenna was so strong willed and full of life. She never had a great relationship with guys due to many factors but mainly due to Mike.<br />Heart Waves is so beautifully written. There's never a moment that you aren't hooked. There isn't that dull chapter or dull scene that some books have. I have to say this is by far one of my favorite books that I have reviewed. I loved how Danielle twisted in the paranormal side to things without over doing it. In many ways you won't even notice it is paranormal, and that is what is so awesome about it. Its never thrown in your face.<br />I couldn't find one thing I hated about this book. Not one, which is rare. Of course I hated Reece there for a little bit toward the end when he is acts idiotic, but then I loved him again. I really enjoyed the little time we had with Tyler. He seems like he will make an interesting character. I can't wait to see more of him in the next 2.<br />BUY THIS BOOK! YOU WILL LOVE IT!</span>
