<span id="freeTextContainer8835636121178022440">3.5 stars<br/><br/>Heart Waves by Danielle Sibarium was a cute read that I enjoyed a lot. The story was easy to get caught up in and the characters overall were pretty great.<br/><br/>The plot was very easy to follow and was very fast paced. The story really captivated me. I loved everything up until the ending, which didn&apos;t seem quite complete to me. There was just a few plot threads I wish had been explored more indepthly, as I would have loved to see how those played out.<br/><br/>I wasn&apos;t the biggest fan of Jenna - she b</span>
  <span id="freeText8835636121178022440" style="display:none">3.5 stars<br /><br />Heart Waves by Danielle Sibarium was a cute read that I enjoyed a lot. The story was easy to get caught up in and the characters overall were pretty great.<br /><br />The plot was very easy to follow and was very fast paced. The story really captivated me. I loved everything up until the ending, which didn't seem quite complete to me. There was just a few plot threads I wish had been explored more indepthly, as I would have loved to see how those played out.<br /><br />I wasn't the biggest fan of Jenna - she bugged me a bit at times, but I did love Grace. I wish she had been in Heart Waves a bit more, as she was a great character. Alex was quite the riot and I loved every scene he showed up in! <br /><br />Heart Waves was a book I read in a day. It was really fast paced and was a cute story. It had a paranormal element, but definitely felt like a contemporary to me. Another great story from Danielle Sibarium.</span>
