        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer426321009" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10714421682288711327">Wow! I’ll start with that! I loved the characters. OMG could Reece BE any sweeter? I LOVE Reece! He’s HOT, SEXY and FUNNY. Oh yeah and SMART and totally PERFECT. I liked that Jenna was strong not a whiny what does he see in me? type of heroine. I thought her ability to know things just from touching them was AWESOME. It’s a different twist on the paranormal side but it didn’t overwhelm the story. <br/><br/>The characters were great and easy to connect with. Even the minor ones, I loved Reece’s brother Aar</span>
  <span id="freeText10714421682288711327" style="display:none">Wow! I’ll start with that! I loved the characters. OMG could Reece BE any sweeter? I LOVE Reece! He’s HOT, SEXY and FUNNY. Oh yeah and SMART and totally PERFECT. I liked that Jenna was strong not a whiny what does he see in me? type of heroine. I thought her ability to know things just from touching them was AWESOME. It’s a different twist on the paranormal side but it didn’t overwhelm the story. <br /><br />The characters were great and easy to connect with. Even the minor ones, I loved Reece’s brother Aaron, and his friend Tyler. Those two REALLY stuck out and hope we get to see a lot more of them in the next book. <br /><br />Overall Heart Waves was a fast paced book that sucked me in from the start. I couldn’t put it down. And now I can’t stop thinking of Reece! I loved it and can’t wait for the sequel to come out!<br /></span>
